  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2011-07-13",
    "date": "2011-10-20T19:12:11Z",
    "text": "Parental Bereavement Act of 2011 - Amends the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993 to entitle an eligible employee to up to 12 workweeks of leave during any 12-month period because of the death of a son or daughter.\n\nAllows such an employee to substitute any available paid leave for any leave without pay.\n\nApplies the same leave entitlement to federal employees."
